President Biden delivered a speech at the Change of Command ceremony for the United States Coast Guard, where Admiral Linda Fagan assumed the role of Commandant. President Biden praised Admiral Fagan's exceptional skill, integrity, and commitment to the country, and highlighted that she is the first woman to lead any branch of the United States Armed Forces. He emphasized the importance of diversity and inclusivity in the military and expressed his gratitude to the Coast Guard for their service in areas such as maritime security, climate change response, and interdicting illicit drug shipments. President Biden also called for creating an environment where every member of the Armed Forces feels safe from sexual assault and harassment. He thanked Admiral Karl Schultz for his leadership as the outgoing Commandant and expressed his confidence in Admiral Fagan's ability to lead the Coast Guard.